alert.note: Alert for Central Coast; Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca; North Coast; Western Strait of Juan De Fuca (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 26 at 3:56AM PST until February 26 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Additional snow accumulations of up to one inch. * WHERE...Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca lowlands, including Port Angeles, Sequim, and Blyn, Western Strait of Juan de Fuca lowlands, including Sekiu, Clallam Bay, and Joyce and North coast, including Neah Bay, Forks, and Queets. * WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning. * IMPACTS...Plan on very difficult travel. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Local accumulations up to 8 inches over higher terrain near the Olympics.
info.instruction: Slow down and use caution while traveling. For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.
